ğŸŒŸ AGENT ENGINEERING STANDARD (AES) - Complete Design & Architecture Document


Author: ouadi Maakoul 

ğŸ›ï¸ 1. FOUNDATIONAL PHILOSOPHY

The "Why" Behind AES

AES exists to solve the Tower of Babel problem in AI agents.

Every organization today is building proprietary agent frameworks that can't talk to each other:

Â· Google has its agent system
Â· Microsoft has AutoGen
Â· OpenAI is building agent frameworks
Â· Startups create bespoke solutions
Â· Researchers build isolated prototypes

Result: Billions wasted on reinventing wheels, massive vendor lock-in, and no way for agents to collaborate across organizational boundaries.

Our Core Beliefs

1. Interoperability is non-negotiable - An agent should work anywhere
2. Observability is safety - You must know what your agents are doing
3. Modularity enables innovation - Swap components without rebuilding everything
4. Open standards win - Proprietary systems eventually fragment and fail

The USB-C Analogy

Think of AES as USB-C for AI agents:

Â· USB-C â†’ One connector that works with phones, laptops, tablets, everything
Â· AES â†’ One interface that works with all agents, all frameworks, all systems

But AES is MORE than just a connectorâ€”it's the entire ecosystem:

Â· The plug (the interface)
Â· The cable (the communication protocol)
Â· The power delivery standard (the security model)
Â· The certification program (the quality assurance)
Â· The ecosystem of compatible devices (the agent marketplace)

