5.3 The Token Scoping System

Traditional approach: Give API key to agent â†’ Agent can do anything.

AES approach:

```python
# BAD: Traditional
api_key = "sk-live-abc123"  # Master key with full access

# GOOD: AES Token Scoping
tokens = {
    "web_search": Token(scopes=["search:read"], max_queries=100/day),
    "database": Token(scopes=["db:read:customers"], tables=["customers"]),
    "email": Token(scopes=["email:send"], recipients=["support@company.com"])
}
```

Each token is:

Â· Scoped: Only does what's needed
Â· Limited: Usage caps per time period
Â· Traceable: Every use logged to specific agent
Â· Revocable: Can be revoked without affecting other agents

